36struct pll_mapping {
37 u8 type;
38 u32 reg;
39};
40
41static struct pll_mapping
42nv04_pll_mapping[] = {
43 { PLL_CORE , 0x680500 },
44 { PLL_MEMORY, 0x680504 },
45 { PLL_VPLL0 , 0x680508 },
46 { PLL_VPLL1 , 0x680520 },
47 { }
48};
49
50static struct pll_mapping
51nv40_pll_mapping[] = {
52 { PLL_CORE , 0x004000 },
53 { PLL_MEMORY, 0x004020 },
54 { PLL_VPLL0 , 0x680508 },
55 { PLL_VPLL1 , 0x680520 },
56 { }
57};
58
59static struct pll_mapping
60nv50_pll_mapping[] = {
61 { PLL_CORE , 0x004028 },
62 { PLL_SHADER, 0x004020 },
63 { PLL_UNK03 , 0x004000 },
64 { PLL_MEMORY, 0x004008 },
65 { PLL_UNK40 , 0x00e810 },
66 { PLL_UNK41 , 0x00e818 },
67 { PLL_UNK42 , 0x00e824 },
68 { PLL_VPLL0 , 0x614100 },

74g84_pll_mapping[] = {
75 { PLL_CORE , 0x004028 },
76 { PLL_SHADER, 0x004020 },
77 { PLL_MEMORY, 0x004008 },
78 { PLL_VDEC , 0x004030 },
79 { PLL_UNK41 , 0x00e818 },
80 { PLL_VPLL0 , 0x614100 },
81 { PLL_VPLL1 , 0x614900 },

85static u16
86pll_limits_table(struct nvkm_bios *bios, u8 *ver, u8 *hdr, u8 *cnt, u8 *len)
87{
88 struct bit_entry bit_C;
89
90 if (!bit_entry(bios, 'C', &bit_C) && bit_C.length >= 10) {
91 u16 data = nvbios_rd16(bios, bit_C.offset + 8);
92 if (data) {
93 *ver = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 0);
94 *hdr = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 1);
95 *len = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 2);
96 *cnt = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 3);
97 return data;
98 }
99 }
100
101 if (bmp_version(bios) >= 0x0524) {
102 u16 data = nvbios_rd16(bios, bios->bmp_offset + 142);
103 if (data) {
104 *ver = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 0);
105 *hdr = 1;
106 *cnt = 1;
107 *len = 0x18;
108 return data;
109 }
110 }
111
112 *ver = 0x00;
113 return 0x0000;
114}
115
116static struct pll_mapping *
117pll_map(struct nvkm_bios *bios)
118{
119 struct nvkm_device *device = bios->subdev.device;
120 switch (device->card_type) {
121 case NV_04:
122 case NV_10:
123 case NV_11:
124 case NV_20:
125 case NV_30:
126 return nv04_pll_mapping;
127 break;
128 case NV_40:
129 return nv40_pll_mapping;
130 case NV_50:
131 if (device->chipset == 0x50)
132 return nv50_pll_mapping;
133 else
134 if (device->chipset < 0xa3 ||
135 device->chipset == 0xaa ||
136 device->chipset == 0xac)
137 return g84_pll_mapping;
138 default:
139 return NULL;
140 }
141}
142
143static u16
144pll_map_reg(struct nvkm_bios *bios, u32 reg, u32 *type, u8 *ver, u8 *len)
145{
146 struct pll_mapping *map;
147 u8 hdr, cnt;
148 u16 data;
149
150 data = pll_limits_table(bios, ver, &hdr, &cnt, len);
151 if (data && *ver >= 0x30) {
152 data += hdr;
153 while (cnt--) {
154 if (nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 3) == reg) {
155 *type = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 0);
156 return data;
157 }
158 data += *len;
159 }
160 return 0x0000;
161 }
162
163 map = pll_map(bios);
164 while (map->reg) {
165 if (map->reg == reg && *ver >= 0x20) {
166 u16 addr = (data += hdr);
167 *type = map->type;
168 while (cnt--) {
169 if (nvbios_rd32(bios, data) == map->reg)
170 return data;
171 data += *len;
172 }
173 return addr;
174 } else
175 if (map->reg == reg) {
176 *type = map->type;
177 return data + 1;
178 }
179 map++;
180 }
181
182 return 0x0000;
183}
184
185static u16
186pll_map_type(struct nvkm_bios *bios, u8 type, u32 *reg, u8 *ver, u8 *len)
187{
188 struct pll_mapping *map;
189 u8 hdr, cnt;
190 u16 data;
191
192 data = pll_limits_table(bios, ver, &hdr, &cnt, len);
193 if (data && *ver >= 0x30) {
194 data += hdr;
195 while (cnt--) {
196 if (nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 0) == type) {
197 *reg = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 3);
198 return data;
199 }
200 data += *len;
201 }
202 return 0x0000;
203 }
204
205 map = pll_map(bios);
206 while (map->reg) {
207 if (map->type == type && *ver >= 0x20) {
208 u16 addr = (data += hdr);
209 *reg = map->reg;
210 while (cnt--) {
211 if (nvbios_rd32(bios, data) == map->reg)
212 return data;
213 data += *len;
214 }
215 return addr;
216 } else
217 if (map->type == type) {
218 *reg = map->reg;
219 return data + 1;
220 }
221 map++;
222 }
223
224 return 0x0000;
225}
226
227int
228nvbios_pll_parse(struct nvkm_bios *bios, u32 type, struct nvbios_pll *info)
229{
230 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &bios->subdev;
231 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
232 u8 ver, len;
233 u32 reg = type;
234 u16 data;
235
236 if (type > PLL_MAX) {
237 reg = type;
238 data = pll_map_reg(bios, reg, &type, &ver, &len);
239 } else {
240 data = pll_map_type(bios, type, &reg, &ver, &len);
241 }
242
243 if (ver && !data)
244 return -ENOENT;
245
246 memset(info, 0, sizeof(*info));
247 info->type = type;
248 info->reg = reg;
249
250 switch (ver) {
251 case 0x00:
252 break;
253 case 0x10:
254 case 0x11:
255 info->vco1.min_freq = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 0);
256 info->vco1.max_freq = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 4);
257 info->vco2.min_freq = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 8);
258 info->vco2.max_freq = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 12);
259 info->vco1.min_inputfreq = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 16);
260 info->vco2.min_inputfreq = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 20);
261 info->vco1.max_inputfreq = INT_MAX;
262 info->vco2.max_inputfreq = INT_MAX;
263
264 info->max_p = 0x7;
265 info->max_p_usable = 0x6;
266
267 /* these values taken from nv30/31/36 */
268 switch (bios->version.chip) {
269 case 0x36:
270 info->vco1.min_n = 0x5;
271 break;
272 default:
273 info->vco1.min_n = 0x1;
274 break;
275 }
276 info->vco1.max_n = 0xff;
277 info->vco1.min_m = 0x1;
278 info->vco1.max_m = 0xd;
279
280 /*
281 * On nv30, 31, 36 (i.e. all cards with two stage PLLs with this
282 * table version (apart from nv35)), N2 is compared to
283 * maxN2 (0x46) and 10 * maxM2 (0x4), so set maxN2 to 0x28 and
284 * save a comparison
285 */
286 info->vco2.min_n = 0x4;
287 switch (bios->version.chip) {
288 case 0x30:
289 case 0x35:
290 info->vco2.max_n = 0x1f;
291 break;
292 default:
293 info->vco2.max_n = 0x28;
294 break;
295 }
296 info->vco2.min_m = 0x1;
297 info->vco2.max_m = 0x4;
298 break;
299 case 0x20:
300 case 0x21:
301 info->vco1.min_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 4) * 1000;
302 info->vco1.max_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 6) * 1000;
303 info->vco2.min_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 8) * 1000;
304 info->vco2.max_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 10) * 1000;
305 info->vco1.min_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 12) * 1000;
306 info->vco2.min_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 14) * 1000;
307 info->vco1.max_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 16) * 1000;
308 info->vco2.max_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 18) * 1000;
309 info->vco1.min_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 20);
310 info->vco1.max_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 21);
311 info->vco1.min_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 22);
312 info->vco1.max_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 23);
313 info->vco2.min_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 24);
314 info->vco2.max_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 25);
315 info->vco2.min_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 26);
316 info->vco2.max_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 27);
317
318 info->max_p = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 29);
319 info->max_p_usable = info->max_p;
320 if (bios->version.chip < 0x60)
321 info->max_p_usable = 0x6;
322 info->bias_p = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 30);
323
324 if (len > 0x22)
325 info->refclk = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 31);
326 break;
327 case 0x30:
328 data = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 1);
329
330 info->vco1.min_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 0) * 1000;
331 info->vco1.max_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 2) * 1000;
332 info->vco2.min_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 4) * 1000;
333 info->vco2.max_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 6) * 1000;
334 info->vco1.min_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 8) * 1000;
335 info->vco2.min_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 10) * 1000;
336 info->vco1.max_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 12) * 1000;
337 info->vco2.max_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 14) * 1000;
338 info->vco1.min_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 16);
339 info->vco1.max_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 17);
340 info->vco1.min_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 18);
341 info->vco1.max_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 19);
342 info->vco2.min_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 20);
343 info->vco2.max_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 21);
344 info->vco2.min_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 22);
345 info->vco2.max_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 23);
346 info->max_p_usable = info->max_p = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 25);
347 info->bias_p = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 27);
348 info->refclk = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 28);
349 break;
350 case 0x40:
351 info->refclk = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 9) * 1000;
352 data = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 1);
353
354 info->vco1.min_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 0) * 1000;
355 info->vco1.max_freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 2) * 1000;
356 info->vco1.min_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 4) * 1000;
357 info->vco1.max_inputfreq = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 6) * 1000;
358 info->vco1.min_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 8);
359 info->vco1.max_m = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 9);
360 info->vco1.min_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 10);
361 info->vco1.max_n = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 11);
362 info->min_p = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 12);
363 info->max_p = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 13);
364 break;
365 default:
366 nvkm_error(subdev, "unknown pll limits version 0x%02x\n", ver);
367 return -EINVAL;
368 }
369
370 if (!info->refclk) {
371 info->refclk = device->crystal;
372 if (bios->version.chip == 0x51) {
373 u32 sel_clk = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x680524);
374 if ((info->reg == 0x680508 && sel_clk & 0x20) ||
375 (info->reg == 0x680520 && sel_clk & 0x80)) {
376 if (nvkm_rdvgac(device, 0, 0x27) < 0xa3)
377 info->refclk = 200000;
378 else
379 info->refclk = 25000;
380 }
381 }
382 }
383
384 /*
385 * By now any valid limit table ought to have set a max frequency for
386 * vco1, so if it's zero it's either a pre limit table bios, or one
387 * with an empty limit table (seen on nv18)
388 */
389 if (!info->vco1.max_freq) {
390 info->vco1.max_freq = nvbios_rd32(bios, bios->bmp_offset + 67);
391 info->vco1.min_freq = nvbios_rd32(bios, bios->bmp_offset + 71);
392 if (bmp_version(bios) < 0x0506) {
393 info->vco1.max_freq = 256000;
394 info->vco1.min_freq = 128000;
395 }
396
397 info->vco1.min_inputfreq = 0;
398 info->vco1.max_inputfreq = INT_MAX;
399 info->vco1.min_n = 0x1;
400 info->vco1.max_n = 0xff;
401 info->vco1.min_m = 0x1;
402
403 if (device->crystal == 13500) {
404 /* nv05 does this, nv11 doesn't, nv10 unknown */
405 if (bios->version.chip < 0x11)
406 info->vco1.min_m = 0x7;
407 info->vco1.max_m = 0xd;
408 } else {
409 if (bios->version.chip < 0x11)
410 info->vco1.min_m = 0x8;
411 info->vco1.max_m = 0xe;
412 }
413
414 if (bios->version.chip < 0x17 ||
415 bios->version.chip == 0x1a ||
416 bios->version.chip == 0x20)
417 info->max_p = 4;
418 else
419 info->max_p = 5;
420 info->max_p_usable = info->max_p;
421 }
422
423 return 0;
424}
